body_html:
@alanchiao I believe that's stft/frame/StridedSlice, not stft/frame/strided_slice.

There are 2 StridedSlice ops created by tf.contrib.signal.stft: example colab. Note that numpy-style slices are StridedSlice ops under the covers.

Here's the op definition for stft/frame/strided_slice which is the node the error message refers to. Its first input is stft/frame/range, which is the result of tf.range(tf.rank(x))

node {
  name: "stft/frame/strided_slice"
  op: "StridedSlice"
  input: "stft/frame/range"
  input: "stft/frame/strided_slice/stack"
  input: "stft/frame/strided_slice/stack_1"
  input: "stft/frame/strided_slice/stack_2"
  attr {
    key: "Index"
    value {
      type: DT_INT32
    }
  }
  attr {
    key: "T"
    value {
      type: DT_INT32
    }
  }
  attr {
    key: "begin_mask"
    value {
      i: 0
    }
  }
  attr {
    key: "ellipsis_mask"
    value {
      i: 0
    }
  }
  attr {
    key: "end_mask"
    value {
      i: 0
    }
  }
  attr {
    key: "new_axis_mask"
    value {
      i: 0
    }
  }
  attr {
    key: "shrink_axis_mask"
    value {
      i: 1
    }
  }
}
